          " إِنَّ الْإِمَامَ إِذَا شَاءَ أَنْ يَعْلَمَ أُعْلِمَ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Abu Ali Al Ashary, from Muhammad Bin Abdul Jabbar, from Safwan, from Ibn Muskan, from Badr Bin Al Waleed, from Abu Al Rabie, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The Imam<sup>asws</sup>, whenever he<sup>asws</sup> so desires to know (something), knows (it)’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            " 2. Abu Ali al-Ash‘ari has narrated from Muhammad ibn ‘Abd al-Jabbar from Safwan from ibn Muskan from Badr ibn al-Walid from Abu al-Rabi‘ from abu ‘Abdallah (a.s.) who has said the following. “Would the Imam (a.s.) want to know he would know.”"
          ]
        }
